Package com.rapidminer.belt.buffer

Class UInt2CategoricalBuffer<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rapidminer.belt.buffer.CategoricalBuffer<T>
      • com.rapidminer.belt.buffer.UInt2CategoricalBuffer<T>
  • public class UInt2CategoricalBuffer<T>
extends CategoricalBuffer<T>
    Implementation of a CategoricalBuffer with category index format IntegerFormats.Format.UNSIGNED_INT2 that can hold 3 different categories. Four category indices are stored in a single byte.
    Author:
    Gisa Meier

        Retrieves the value at the given index. This method is thread-safe and can be used alongside invocations of CategoricalBuffer.set(int, T) and CategoricalBuffer.setSave(int, T). However, this method might not return the latest value set on another thread.

      • set

        public void set​(int index,
                T value)
        Sets the data at the given index to the given value.

        Due to the compressed integer format, this method is only thread-safe for indices with different results when divided by 4. Values can be lost when writing at indices index1 and index2 with index1/4 == index2/4 from different threads. So when writing in batches of indices [m,n) from different threads, you must ensure that m and n are divisible by 4.

        Specified by:
        set in class CategoricalBuffer<T>
        Parameters:
        index - the index where the value should be set
        value - the value to set

      • setSave

        public boolean setSave​(int index,
                       T value)
        Tries to set the data at the given index to the given value. Returns true if it worked and false if the buffer format cannot hold any more different values.

        Due to the compressed integer format, this method is only thread-safe for indices with different results when divided by 4. Values can be lost when writing at indices index1 and index2 with index1/4 == index2/4 from different threads. So when writing in batches of indices [m,n) from different threads, you must ensure that m and n are divisible by 4.

        Specified by:
        setSave in class CategoricalBuffer<T>
        Parameters:
        index - the index where the value should be set
        value - the value to set
        Returns:
        false if the buffer contained already to many different values to take this value, true otherwise

      • toBooleanColumn

        public CategoricalColumn<T> toBooleanColumn​(ColumnType<T> type,
                                            T positiveValue)
        Description copied from class: CategoricalBuffer
        Creates a boolean column with the given positive value if the dictionary has at most two values. The positive value must be either one of the dictionary values, making the other value, if it exists, negative. Or in case of a dictionary with only one value the positive value can be null making the only value negative.
        Specified by:

        Parameters:

        positiveValue - the positive value or null
